1) Generate configuration

   autoconf -f
   ./configure --enable-userlevel --disable-linuxmodule --host=mips64-octeon-linux-gnu --build=i686-linux --enable-tools=mixed --enable-octeon --enable-user-multithread

2) Build Linux usermode click with octeon

  Assumed: OCTEON_MODEL and OCTEON_ROOT environs are set!

    cd userlevel
    make

3) Transfer files to octeon

  The click executable and ping echo responder click script.  In
  script octeon/echo-align.click, edit the IP/MAC address in
  addressinfo() to match your device (to /root/)

  click
  octeon/echo-align.click

4) Boot the octeon, login as root

  Start app on octeon

    ./click echo-align.click

  On linux

    ping octeon

5) Additional octeon configuration options

  The patch adds the following usermode click octeon specific command
  line options:

      --no-octeon-wptr          Allocate WQE before packet buffer.
      --no-octeon-red           Disable Random Early Drop.
      --no-octeon-dynrs         Disable short packet in WQE.
